==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mezzo-soprano
<hw>Mez"zo-so*pra"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>Having a medium compass between the soprano and contralto; -- said
of the voice of a female singer.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A mezzo-soprano voice.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
person having such a voice.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mezzotint</ent>⟦br⟧
